  <heading>DUPQ</heading>
  <desc>
    <brief>
      <para>Broadcast indexed element within each quadword vector segment (unpredicated)</para>
    </brief>
    <authored>
      <para>This instruction unconditionally broadcasts the indexed element within each
128-bit source vector segment to all elements
of the corresponding destination vector segment.
This instruction is unpredicated.</para>
      <para>The immediate element index is in the range of 0 to 15 (bytes), 7
(halfwords), 3 (words) or 1 (doublewords).</para>
    </authored>
    <predicated>False</predicated>
    <uses_dit condition="FEAT_SVE2 is implemented or FEAT_SME is implemented">True</uses_dit>
  </desc>
  <operationalnotes>
    <operationalnote>
      <operationalnote_content>
        <para>This instruction is a data-independent-time instruction as described in <xref linkend="ARMARM_BEICCDDAB3">About PSTATE.DIT</xref>.</para>
      </operationalnote_content>
    </operationalnote>
  </operationalnotes>
